Demonstrate the use of following PaaS tools: Cloud Foundry / GoogleApp Engine/ OpenShift with a database application.

Install Google App Engine SDK
./google-cloud-sdk/install.sh
./google-cloud-sdk/bin/gcloud init
gcloud components install app-engine-python

In Eclipse:
“Create ‘src’ folder and add it to PYTHONPATH“.
Give path of Google App Engine installed directory till google_appengine
Choose “Hello Webapp World” template to generate the sample files.
For running:
“Run As” –> “Run Configuration”, create a new “PyDev Google App Run“.
Main tab -> Main module, manually type the directory path of “dev_appserver.py“.
Arguments tab -> Program arguments, put “${project_loc}/src“.
